9. Rb1 c5
{ Expanding in the center. We sometimes need to spend time rerouting the Na6 before starting active play, but here it can actually go to b4 quite often, e.g. }
10. Nf3 cxd4 11. exd4 Bf5 12. O-O Nb4
{ It is annoying for White to deal with the pressure on the a2 and c2-pawns. }
