1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4
{ The dreaded London. I have now spent quite a bit of time trying to figure it out for the course, and I can tell you my intense hatred for it has only increased. }
2... g6
{ We're playing 2...g6 for one major reason. White can start with @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pppppppp/5n2/8/3P4/8/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 1 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Nf3  , and as honorable Grünfeld aficionados, we're obliged to reply with  2...g6  , which, after  3.Bf4  , locks us into the fianchetto setups. Therefore, I feel that spending time to learn the other replies to 2.Bf4 is, let's say, an unnecessary investment of time and effort on both mine and your part. }
3. Nc3
{ 3.f3?!  is a very odd move here, and we should welcome it wholeheartedly.  3...d5  4.Nc3  c5  .  The plan of pushing e4 is dead and with it so is any justification for 3.f3. }
3... d5 4. Qd2
{ A logical move, intending both Bh6 and O-O-O, but as you will see, actuallycastling long is likely to cause White grief, and Bh6 can be dealt with quite easily. }
4... Bg7 5. Bh6 Bxh6
{ 5...O-O  is also fine, but the text move is more concrete. } 6. Qxh6 Bf5 7.
O-O-O { White allows us to get a good endgame straight away. } 7... Ng4 8. Qg7
{ A good-looking move but in fact, the queen will soon be in trouble. } 8...
Rf8 9. Nh3 Nd7
{ Note also how annoying the Ng4 is when White had to play Nh3 to protect f2. It can't be driven away easily since f3 always runs into ...Ne3. }
10. Qxh7 e6 11. f3 g5 12. Qg7 Ne3
{ We're in control. After  13.Nxg5  Qe7!  we don’t even need to cash in on d1. The plan of ...O-O-O and then perhaps ...Qb4 and ...Nc4, with a mating attack, is stronger.  14.Nh7  is more or less the only move as  14.g4?  O-O-O!  15.gxf5  Nxf5!  loses on the spot.  @@StartFEN@@r3kr2/pppnqpQN/4p3/3p1b2/3P4/2N1nP2/PPP1P1PP/2KR1B1R b q - 2 14@@EndFEN@@  14...Bxh7  15.Qxh7  and now we can choose between  15...Nxd1  with a very good game, and  15...Nb6!  which might be even stronger, aiming to  keep the Ne3 there, by supporting it with ...Nbc4 if needed, and then we can start on the mating attack with ...Qb4. }
