[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. Bg5
{ This used to be a very popular line − in fact, I played a decent amount of it myself with White, in my Colle-blighted youth. By 2022, it is very clearly a poor relative of the London in terms of volume and general perception, but it remains very playable, of course.  In effect, we'll be playing the Réti Opening a tempo down @@StartBracket@@imagine the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.Nf3  d5  2.g3  Bg4  3.Bg2  Nf6  lines with reversed colors@@EndBracket@@.   The extra tempo makes White's life quite comfortable in that comparison, of course, but the nature of the positions we will see in this chapter is slow enough for us not to have to worry about tempi all that much.  Conceptually, Black has two major approaches to this line: we can play ...d6 or ...d5, and that will, to a very large extent, define our next plans. I believe the ...d5 systems are fine, but I personally always preferred setups with ...d6, and this is what I will be recommending, in particular with a view to playing ...c5, ...cxd4, and pushing for a reasonably early ...e7-e5.   @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pppppp1p/5np1/8/3P4/5N2/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nc3  − this move order more or less forces us to play  3...d5  since we don't really want to play the pure Pirc.  4.Bg5  transposes after  4...Bg7  , but even stronger is  4...Ne4!  grabbing the initiative. }
3... Bg7 4. Nc3 d5 5. e3 O-O 6. Be2 h6
{ It turns out that having an option of playing ...g6-g5 will be very useful later.   6...c5  7.dxc5  Nbd7  is also playable but I prefer the text move. Less good is @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/pp2ppbp/5np1/2Pp2B1/8/2N1PN2/PPP1BPPP/R2QK2R b KQ - 0 7@@EndFEN@@  7...Qa5  8.O-O  e6  9.e4!  Nxe4  10.Nxe4  dxe4  11.Nd2!  when White is better. }
7. Bf4 c5 8. dxc5 Nbd7
{ This is a position from my game vs. Fabi in STL 2021, but with the move ...h6 included, which I believe favors Black. }
9. Nxd5 Nxd5 10. Qxd5 g5
{ It is very important to disconnect the white bishop from the h6-pawn before we cash in on the Q-side. }
11. Bg3 Bxb2 12. O-O { Castling doesn't work at all now. } 12... Bxa1 13. Rxa1
Qa5 14. Nd4 Qxc5 15. Nf5 Kh7
{ Black is simply better as an exchange is still worth something! } *

