Symmetrical Grünfeld, leaving only the 5th moves in this chapter. }
5... d5 6. Nc3
{ A sensible enough move − White is playing a King's Indian with an extra tempo, and developing pieces to normal squares can never be too bad. But Black has a number of efficient solutions and the one I like the most is the text move. }
6... d4 { 6...c5  is of course not a mistake either. } 7. Na4 e5 8. c3
{ Of course not  8.Nxe5?  Qe8! } 8... Re8
{ Our plan here is quite simple. We want to finish development with ...Nc6 @@StartBracket@@or even, in some cases, ...Na6, creating threats against the Na4@@EndBracket@@, and then play in the center, while White is still struggling for a constructive plan. }
9. e4 dxe3 10. Bxe3 Na6 11. Re1 c6 { Black is doing quite well. } *

