Bxb2 11. Rb1 Bf6 { Having the e7-pawn protected will help in a few lines. } 12.
Qa4 Qd7 { A very nice tactical way to solve all of our issues. } 13. Bxc5 b6
14. Bxb6 Nd4 { This motif again! } 15. Qd1 axb6 16. Nxd4 Rxa2
{ We have a weakness on b6, which would be a problem if we weren't so active. }
17. Qb3 Rd2 18. Qb4 Ra2
{ This is an immediate draw by repetition after  19.Qb3  Rd2  etc.   An attempt to play for a win with  18...Rxd3!?  runs into a very beautiful riposte:  19.Ne6!!   19.exd3  Bxd4  isn't much worse at all for White, but I think most people would choose Black here.  19...Qxe6  20.exd3  and the b6-pawn will fall. We're still fine  after  20...Qd7  , but there is no chance of us winning the game, of course. My thanks to Alina for pointing out this cute line to me. }
*

