{ A very important move. We're not interested in taking on e5 with the bishop, of course @@StartBracket@@at least not for a while yet@@EndBracket@@, but creating the threat of ...Nd7 does a great job of discouraging the most logical follow up White has, which is Be3. }
16. Bf3 { 16.b3  Nd7!  is immediately equal. } 16... c6 17. Be3 Nd3
{ The position is fine for us straight away, which the line  18.Nxd3  Rxe3  19.Rad1  Bf5  indicates. Black has sufficient compensation. }
