16. Bd2 { 16.b3  Nd7!  is immediately equal. } 16... Bf5
{ Calmly continuing to develop pieces, we don't need to cash in our threats just yet.  16...Nd7?!  17.Bf3  would be too early. }
17. Bf3 c6
{ Bf3 is always met by ...c6, restricting the bishop, and now, very much intending to go in with Nd3. }
18. g4 Be6 19. b3 { Now we have to resort to tactics. } 19... Nd3 20. Nxd3 Bxa1
21. Rxa1 Rad8 22. Nc5 { 22.Be2?  Bxc4!!  actually loses for White. } 22... Rxd2
23. Ne4 Rd3 24. Nf6+ Kf8 25. Nxe8 Rxf3 { We're easily fine here. } *

