{ The only source of counterplay left for us here. Time is short, if White gets to play Be2 we won't be able to challenge that setup at all. }
11. Bf4 Bd4 12. Bg3 Qc5
{ We have to go all-in as giving White a tempo to finish development would effectively end the game. }
13. Qf3 Nf6 14. Be2
{ 14.Qd3  Ng4  would lead to transpositions after either  15.Qe2  or  15.Qf3  . }
14... Bg4 15. Qd3 Na6
{ We need to be as active as possible, and this move creates a double idea of ...Nb4 and ...Rad8. }
16. Bxg4 Nb4 { Pushing the queen further back before recapturing. } 17. Qf3
{ Loses after a long but very forced sequence. } 17... Nc2+ 18. Ke2 Nxa1 19.
Rxa1 Bxc3 20. bxc3 Nxe4 21. Nxe4 Qxc4+ { White's position collapses. } *

