{ Giving ourselves a very important option of ...Rb6 for future use. } 15. Be2
Nc7 16. Qb1 Rb6 17. Qc2 Bxf3 18. Bxf3 Nb5 19. O-O
{ If  19.Bd2?  Na3!  20.Qa4  Ra6  followed by ...Qxd3 and Black is clearly better. }
19... Nxc3 20. Bxc5 Rc6 21. Bxa7 Nxe4 22. Qd1 Rxc1 23. Qxc1 Nc3
{ Occupying a very nice c3-square with the knight further restricts White’s options, taking away some squares from the f1-rook.   I would also prefer not to allow the pin on this knight which could happen in case of  23...Qxd3  24.Re1  . We’re also  generally more interested in winning the a2-pawn, rather than the one on d3. }
