{ I don't like  14...Bxb2  at all. White has a number of very promising options, from the prosaic  15.Rb1  Bg7  16.d4  to the more romantic @@StartFEN@@r2qr1k1/ppp2p1p/n1n3p1/1N6/4P3/P2PBP2/1b2BP1P/R2QK2R w KQ - 0 15@@EndFEN@@  15.d4!?  Bxa1  16.Qxa1  Na5  17.h4  followed by h5, with a very strong initiative. }
