{ Faster than starting with  7...c6  −  the fact that the bishop is on d3, in the way of the Qd1, means we can use the unprotected Nd4 to speed up our central play even more. }
8. exd5 c6 9. Nc3 { 9.Bg5  cxd5  10.Nc3  transposes to the9.Nc3 line. } 9...
cxd5 10. Bg5 h6 11. Bh4 Nc6 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. cxd5 cxd5
{ This position is weirdly reminiscent of the Four Knights positions I used to get 25 years ago, but Black is very well equipped for it, with the bishop already on g7, and the option of ...g6-g5 open for later. Our immediate plans include ...Rb8, ...Be6, and then we can consider further. }
*

