{ I believe this to be a bit stronger than  7...Rb8  as it gives us the option to recapture on c5 with the d-pawn. That is relevant in the variation  @@StartFEN@@r2qk1nr/pb2ppbp/1pnp2p1/2p5/1PP5/P1N3P1/3PPPBP/1RBQK1NR w Kkq - 0 8@@EndFEN@@  8.bxc5  Bxc3!  9.dxc3  dxc5  with a very big positional advantage. }
