{ White gets some temporary initiative for the pawn, but we're easily going to be able to finish development, with a good game. }
12. Qa4+ { The check doesn't really give White anything. } 12... Nbc6 13. Qa3
{ Trying to put pressure on the d6-pawn, plus White generally needs to be able to recapture on b2 with a queen since play is very often connected with ideas of Ne4, and pressure along the a1-h8 diagonal. }
13... O-O 14. Ne4 Nf5 { We're comfortably parrying the threats. } *

