2... c5 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 Nc6
{ The starting position of the symmetrical c4/c5 English. White's main option here, by far, is  5.Nf3  , but these days you have to be ready for many other attempts, including some very quirky ones, such as  5.b3  . }
