5. Bxf6 Nxf6 6. Nf3 g6 7. e4 dxe4 8. Nxe4 c6
{ The machine insists  8...c6  is somehow more precise than 8...Bg7, but both give us a small edge with our bishop pair and a solid structure, much like a very good Caro. Speaking of which,  9.Nxf6+  exf6  is an exchange we don't mind. It liberates  our f8-bishop and the f6-pawn does a good job covering the e5-square. On top of that, just imagine how safe our king will be once it finds shelter on the kingside! }
