[White "17. London System 2.Bf4 g6 3.Nc3 − 4th moves"]
[Black "Jobava London 3.Bf4 c5 − Alternative"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 { Threatening 3.e4, so our reply is semi-forced here. } 2...
d5
{ The big negative effect of playing Nc3 so early, with the pawn back on c2, is that White won't be able to challenge our center with c4 any time soon. And for that very same reason, we're even happier than usual pushing ...c5 ourselves. }
3. Bf4 c5
{ As a safe backup line, I would suggest playing the text move.   After  3...g6  , we will transpose to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pppppppp/5n2/8/3P4/8/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 1 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Bf4  g6  3.Nc3  d5  in order to preserve continuity throughout the course. }
4. e3 cxd4 5. exd4 Bg4 6. f3 { 6.Qd2  Nc6  is also quite comfy for us. } 6...
Bd7
{ Provoking f3 limits White's options, especially the development of the g1-knight, while we want to play ...e6, ...Nc6, ...a6, ... b5 and have a solid game. }
