9. exf6 { Accepting the gambit. } 9... Nxf6 10. dxc5 Nc6
{ We're not even going to try winning the pawn back, our plan is to push in the center, using the fact that White is very restricted for compensation. }
11. Be2 e5 12. O-O h6
{ Taking away the g5-square and planning ...Bf5, ...Ng4 etc. Even the occasional ...g5-g4 might become a plan. This is a very sharp and interesting position I quite like the look of. }
