{ 10.Nb3  is now too slow since after  10...Qc7  the e5-pawn is weak.  The attempt to overprotect the pawn with  11.Bd4  is the classical story of the cure being worse than the disease. Following  11...b6  12.Be2  , Black is spoiled for choice. Both plans of  12....Rd8  13.O-O  d6  or @@StartFEN@@r1b2rk1/p1qpppbp/1p2n1p1/4P2n/3B4/1NP2N2/PP2BPPP/R2QK2R b KQ - 1 12@@EndFEN@@  12...Bb7  13.O-O  Nhf4  are in Black's favor. White's pieces are suboptimally placed and  the e5-pawn is a liability. }
10... d6 11. exd6 Qxd6 { We are fine. } *

