{ 3.f3?!  is a very odd move here, and we should welcome it wholeheartedly.  3...d5  4.Nc3  c5  .  The plan of pushing e4 is dead and with it so is any justification for 3.f3. }
3... Bg7 4. Nbd2 c5
{ I think this is slightly cleaner than  4...O-O  5.c3!  and then we're choosing between  5...c5  6.dxc5!  Na6  7.Nb3  and @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/ppppppbp/5np1/8/3P1B2/2P2N2/PP1NPPPP/R2QKB1R b KQ - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5...d6  6.e4  , both of which I am not entirely happy with. }
5. c3 cxd4 6. cxd4 Qb6
{ It's important to lure the knight to c4 since that stops the e4 plans from White, and the knight is generally not great there. }
7. Rc1 O-O 8. Nc4 Qd8 9. e3 d6
{ We're obviously not interested in justifying Nc4 by playing ...d5 and driving it to an excellent e5-square. }
10. h3 Nc6
{ We'll start pushing back soon. Note that  11.d5  will run into  11...Nb4  and is therefore not a threat at all. }
*

