3... Bg7 4. e3 O-O 5. h3
{ A major part of White’s game plan in these lines is keeping this bishop alive, and this move provides it with a very safe haven on h2. }
5... d6 6. c3 Nfd7
{ This move order is quite tricky, and it's a rare case of a position where I won't be recommending ...c5.   6...c5  7.dxc5  very importantly, with the pawn already on c3, we no longer have any ...Nd5/...Nh5 tactics to use here.  7...dxc5  8.Nbd2  is a surprisingly annoying position for Black. I wouldn't say we definitely won't equalize in the long run, but I don't really like it and decided to deviate. }
