9. cxd4
{ White quite happily takes on d4 with this pawn since it allows Nc3 later, but we're still fine.  9.exd4  Nc6  with ...e5 to follow is good for us. }
9... Qb6 10. Nc3
{ An interesting move, but this is where we cash in the ...g6-g5 option. }
10... g5 { 10...Qxb2?  11.Bxf6  Bxf6  12.Nd5+-  our queen won't come back. }
11. Bg3 Qxb2 12. Nb5 Na6
{ We want to play ...Bf5 and the queen will be safe on b2. } 13. Bd3 Bd7
{ It turns out that White can't get to the queen in time, resulting in a number of lines that end in perpetual, for instance  14.e4  Rfc8  15.Rb1  Qxa2  16.e5  Nd5  17.Ra1  Qb2=  . }
*

