6. dxc5 Qc7 7. Nbd2 { This move is surprisingly venomous. } 7... Qxc5 8. Bxf6
Bxf6 9. Ne4 Qb6 10. Nxf6+ Qxf6
{ The position may look dry at first, but White's next move forces us to take things seriously. }
11. h4 d6 12. h5 { The engine holds with the calm: } 12... Nc6 13. Qd5 Ne5 14.
Be2 Rb8
