3... Bg7 4. e3 c5 5. c3 { 5.Nbd2  transposes to the4.Nbd2 move order. } 5...
O-O
{ We're not taking on d4 just yet since it works a lot better once White can't put the knight on c3 after recapturing with the c3-pawn. Therefore, in most cases, we will be waiting for Nbd2 before we do that.   5...Qb6  6.Qb3  d6  ,  with ideas of ...Be6, is playable, but in the end, I chose a different path. }
6. Bd3 d6 7. Nbd2 Nc6 8. Qc2
{ This has been played quite a bit, with a very optimistic nod towards perhaps castling long, but it's not a good move. }
8... cxd4 9. exd4 Nd5
{ 9...e5?  10.dxe5  dxe5  was seen in Thorfinnsson-Nepomniachtchi, chess.com 2019.  This is a good example to demonstrate why it's important to include ...h6 before pushing ...e5 since White missed a chance to get a large advantage by playing  11.Ne4! }
10. O-O h6 11. Bh4 Nf4 12. Rfe1 Qc7
{ The text is even stronger than cashing in the  12...Nxd3  option. } 13. Bf1
e5
{ With a very nice game for Black − we have already seized the initiative and are currently threatening ...Nxd4 since the pawn on c3 is pinned. }
*

