{ We're not taking on d4 just yet since it works a lot better once White can't put the knight on c3 after recapturing with the c3-pawn. Therefore, in most cases, we will be waiting for Nbd2 before we do that.   5...Qb6  6.Qb3  d6  ,  with ideas of ...Be6, is playable, but in the end, I chose a different path. }
6. Bd3 d6 7. Nbd2 Nc6 8. Bxf6 Bxf6
{ 8...exf6!?  This is perhaps the only position where I'll allow it. After  9.O-O  b6  10.Re1  f5  the machine actually suggests we're a bit better. }
