11. dxe5 dxe5 12. Qe2 Qc7 { Defending the pawn and unpinning the Nf6. } 13.
Rad1 Nh5 14. Bg3 f5
{ The bishop on g3 is in some trouble and we also have a plan of trading it and pushing ...e5-e4 if we want. Black was already better in Meier-Ivic, chess.com 2020. }
