10. O-O O-O 11. Re1 e5
{ 11...Qc7  12.d5  is a bit less precise since the inclusion of ...Qc7 and Re1 makes ...dxe5 less potent  after  12...Ne5  13.Nxe5  . }
12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Be4 Qc7 14. Qe2
{ Our e5-pawn is weak − luckily for us, we're not obliged to care. } 14... Bg7
15. Bxc6 bxc6 16. Nxe5 Re8 { This is just bad for White. } *

