{ A very similar variation to the6.Nxd4 line, with the difference being that the Nc4 is a bit better for White in the following line. }
8. Nf5 gxf5 9. Qxd5
{ Controlling the a5 and d6-squares, makes the possible ...e6 counterplay harder to realize. However, Black has a very good option here. }
9... Nb4 10. Qd1 Nc6
{ The threat of ...b5! more or less forces White to repeat with  11.Qd5  Nb4  . }
