8. Ne4 { 8.Ng5?  d5  9.exd6  O-O!  is precisely why we played 7...Bg7. } 8...
Nc6 9. Bg5 O-O { We can't allow Nd6+, of course. } 10. h4 h6
{ We don't need to remove the e5-pawn to free up our own play. And if I'm honest, the final position of the line is crazy enough to make me forgive this move for usurping the place of  10...Nxe5  . }
11. h5 { Absolutely the only way to continue. } 11... hxg5 12. hxg6 e6
{ Of course, the Bb3 needs to be neutralized asap. } 13. gxf7+
{ Once again, the only way to continue the attack. In fact, White's next few moves are all but forced. }
13... Rxf7 14. Nd6 { Black can just ignore the threat. } 14... Qe7 15. Nxf7
Qxf7 16. Nxg5 Qg6 { We're ready to assume control. } *

