{ White does generate the threat of Nxc6 but can be safely met by simply taking on d4. }
12... cxd4 13. exd4 dxc4
{ Having unloaded some of the pressure in the center, we're once again ready to finish development. Note that none of the pawn grabs is worrisome:   A@@EndBracket@@  14.Nxc6  Qd5  15.Ne5  O-O  ,  followed by ...Bb7, gives Black a serious edge.   B@@EndBracket@@  14.Nxc4  is met by  14...Qc3  . @@StartBracket@@The issue with  14...Qd5  is  15.Be5  f6  16.Ne3  and White untangles successfully.@@EndBracket@@ With the queen on c3, the same @@StartFEN@@r1b1k2r/p3ppbp/2p3p1/8/2NP1B2/2q5/P1P2PPP/R2Q1RK1 w kq - 1 15@@EndFEN@@  15.Be5  idea doesn't work due to  15...f6  when White loses serious material. }
