{ In my own games, I have always played  2...Ne4  , but that's mainly due to inertia and laziness. The text move is much more sensible. }
3. e3 { 3.Nc3  would transpose to theVeresov chapter. } 3... c5 4. c3 Qb6
{ A typically annoying move for White − the pawn on b2 being unprotected is often a drawback of developing the Bc1 too early. }
5. Qb3 { 6.Qc2  Nc6  7.Nd2  e5!  8.dxe5  Nxe5  is quite nice for Black. } 5...
c4 6. Qc2
{ 6.Qxb6  axb6  7.Nd2  b5  is good for us, due to a very heavy bind we have on the Q-side. }
6... Ne4 7. Bf4 Bf5 8. Qc1 Nc6
{ We're way ahead in development. White should push back a bit. } 9. f3 Nf6 10.
e4 { Black can calmly retreat. } 10... Bg6 11. Be3 e6
{ Our spacial edge is still good enough for a very healthy position. } *

