2... d5
{ In my own games, I have always played  2...Ne4  , but that's mainly due to inertia and laziness. The text move is much more sensible. }
3. Nd2 { 3.Nc3  would transpose to theVeresov chapter. } 3... c5 4. e3 cxd4
{ We're going for the tempo play here since White's setup is very sturdy, and will start making decent sense if we allow c3, Bd3, and then perhaps even f4 followed by Ngf3. }
