[Result "*"]

1. g3 d5
{ The most consistent way of playing against 1.g3. We're immediately beginning the fight for the center.  1...e5  would also be quite logical if not for the fact that  2.c4  , pivoting into the English, exists. }
2. d4 g6 { Or  2...Nf6  , but full symmetry works as well. } 3. Bg2 Bg7
{ This leads to either the Symmetrical Grünfeld or the Nf3/g3/d4 Tabiya, which is the subject of the next chapter. }
4. Nf3 { 4.c4  c6  is the Grünfeld. } 4... Nf6 5. O-O O-O
{ This position is a verybig topic, and will be covered separately. } *

