12. f4 { The most ambitious try. } 12... a4
{ I like this cold reaction, even though Dubov's version  12...Nd7  13.f5  gxf5  14.Nxf5  Bxf5  15.Rxf5  e6  16.Rff1  f5!  as in Wang Hao-Dubov, St. Petersburg 2018, isn't bad at all either. }
13. f5 Bc8
{ We've calmly absorbed the f5 push and are now ready for our own play. In particular, I'd like to try to get the b8-knight to f6, but in more general terms it's unclear what White achieved here while clearly weakening the king, apart from pushing our bishop back for a time. }
