1. b3 e5 { Let's play in the center and show them how it's done. } 2. Bb2 Nc6
3. e3 Nf6 { Continuing to develop pieces is never going to be a mistake. } 4.
Bb5 { The old main line. } 4... e4
{ This is the newer way of treating the position. People used to feel obliged to play  4...Bd6  5.Na3  Na5  here, getting into the nonsense spirit of the entire line, but this is better, I believe. }
5. Ne2 a6 6. Bxc6 dxc6 7. Ng3 h5
{ As usual, this push is a very good way to start questioning the knight on g3. }
8. Nc3 Bg4 { The more direct option compared to  8...Qe7!? } 9. f3
{ 9.Nge2  Qd7  as in Karjakin-Caruana, Saint Louis 2017 is excellent for Black with ...O-O-O and ...h5-h4 incoming while White still has trouble castling. }
9... exf3 10. gxf3
{ And now, in Nakamura-Vidit, chess24.com 2021, Black should play: } 10... h4
11. fxg4
{ 11.Nge4?  Nxe4  12.Nxe4  Bh5  is good for us and ...f5 followed by ...Qd5 is the current threat. }
11... hxg3 12. h3 g2 13. Rg1 Rxh3 14. Qe2 { White isn't doing poorly at all. }
