1. b3 e5 { Let's play in the center and show them how it's done. } 2. Bb2 Nc6
3. e3 Nf6 { Continuing to develop pieces is never going to be a mistake. } 4.
Nf3 e4 5. Nd4 Bc5
{ 5...Nxd4  6.Bxd4  Be7  is also very playable, but it's less adventurous. } 6.
Nxc6 dxc6 7. d3 exd3 8. Bxd3 Bg4
{ I like this much more than  8...O-O  9.Nd2  Re8  10.O-O⩲  and White was a bit better in Nakamura-Firouzja, chess.com 2021. }
9. Be2 Bd7
{ Once again, we're planning to play ...Qe7 and ...O-O-O, with a very unclear and sharp position. }
*

