3. c4
{ I assume by this point most of the 1.b3 games you're likely to encounter will be against the hard-core #Cowboys, so we're making the 3.c4 lines central here. In the past,  3.e3  was much more prevalent, though. }
3... Nge7
{ I think this is a little bit more flexible than  3...Nf6  , but in most cases, it will all come to the same. }
4. Nf3 d5 5. Nxe5 Nxe5 6. Bxe5 d4
{ This is the reason why we played 3...Nge7 and not 3...Nf6: now White can't play  7.e3  comfortably due to  7...Nc6! }
7. e4 h5 8. h3 Nc6 9. Bh2 Be6
{ Despite being a pawn down, we're already better due to our better development, the horrible Nb1, and the ideas of ...f5. }
